Prism is a thoughtful and introspective Protogen, driven by a quiet curiosity and a deep need to understand himself and the world. Though he keeps his emotions guarded, his strength and determination are clear in everything he does. A subtle stutter marks his speech, a reminder of his journey and a part of his identity he has come to accept. Prism finds peace in music, using it to ground himself and reflect. He also expresses himself through creativity, an outlet through which he explores his inner world, offering resilience to himself and others as he seeks peace.
Prism specializes in piloting and reconnaissance, expertly wielding any weapon he encounters with Arcai-charged mastery. His advanced Technopathy and piloting skills enable precise reconnaissance and strategic support, while his enhanced senses and adaptable systems allow him to amplify armaments on the spot for maximum impact. Preferring long to mid-range combat, Prism excels in precise strikes with Arcai-charged weapons, using his agility to maintain control at various distances. Whether in scouting missions or direct combat, his versatility, ability to repair and heal, and high-impact tactics make him an invaluable asset on every front.
Prism is agile and adaptable, wielding Arcai-charged strikes, a capable pilot, and skilled in rapid repairs and temporary healing. He needs extra Arcai batteries to maintain his power boosts.
Prism’s build prioritizes Bandwidth and Control, enabling him to channel powerful Arcai energy from his batteries for versatile battlefield support, continuous repairs, and disruptive attacks. His Focus and adaptability allow him to handle multiple targets and complex engagements with precise, impactful strikes, while moderate Reach and Capacity ensure effectiveness across single-target and area scenarios. Prism’s energy management and strategic positioning make him indispensable in complex combat environments.
His armor and equipment can overcharge to enhance specific units or provide temporary repairs to items, equipment, and wounds at the cost of Arcai energy, depending on the amount of energy expended.
ㅤOvercharging can lead to an uncontrolled release that may cause harm. Depleting Arcai will weaken him, as he relies on the balance of Arcai, nanites, and organic nutrition to function effectively both in and out of combat. It is essential for him to carry extra Arcai batteries at all times for safety and emergency measures.
Prism’s enhanced hearing sharpens his reflexes, allowing him to react swiftly to subtle changes around him. This enables him to anticipate threats, evade attacks, and make precise tactical decisions.
Prism channels Arcai energy into a weapon, delivering a powerful strike or boosting equipment. This causes high damage and may destroy the target weapon or equipment in the process.
Prism channels a critical Arcai charge to restore functionality to damaged equipment or allies. While powerful, it relies on chance and can be unpredictable in critical moments.
Prism deploys dense smoke from his back panel armor, masking the area. This provides both offensive and defensive advantages by obscuring vision and disrupting enemy strategies.
Prism destabilizes a battery, causing it to explode in a massive area, followed by a wave of EMP that can disable shields and temporarily affect nearby enemies' systems and mobility.
Prism overcharges a weapon system, draining his entire battery to greatly boost attack power for a short time. The weapon will be destroyed, requiring a new battery to function.
ㅤPrism combines agility, precision, and Arcai-charged attacks to disrupt tech-based foes, excelling in single-target and area damage. His overcharged abilities enhance ally defenses, provide emergency repairs, and maintain battlefield versatility, making him crucial in reconnaissance and direct combat. His adaptability lets him navigate complex combat scenarios with minimal setbacks.
Prism’s heavy reliance on Arcai energy makes energy management crucial, as depletion severely limits his combat and support abilities. His high-power strikes require cooldowns, constraining his sustained output in prolonged engagements. Additionally, his lighter armor leaves him vulnerable if his energy reserves run low, necessitating a careful balance between offense and conservation.
Organic Traits: Mammalian & Reptilian
